Last day with sonnets

We might do functions today, maybe not.

Types vs Token distinction Names in a table are the types, what are being counted are tokens.

Next month we will work on steming words - mapping multiple tenses to one type.

TTR - Type Token Ratio Ratio of unique word types and total number of tokens divide types by tokens and multiply by 100 to talk in percentages. Lower TTR indicates less variety

Mean Word Frequency (MWF) Number of times any word is used on average (number of tokens divided by types) MWF indicates the rate at which word types are reused. A higher MWF may indicate less variety.

Sonnets 14 lines Iambic pentameter Up to 140 words in a sonnet

Talking about the Types and Tokens of outlier sonnets
